1. Z0 {Hello, dear student! Thank you for buying my course! I’m Hungarian Grandmaster Peter Leko and I’d like to invite you to an epic journey throughout my three decades of experience in the Ruy Lopez or Spanish Opening. I picked up the Classical Spanish at 12 and became a GM at 14 — the youngest in history at that time. I started playing against the very best players in the world and learned a tremendous amount of nuances from legendary masters like World Champion Boris Spassky. And here, I want to provide you with the understanding I’ve gathered over more than 30 years. Why the Spanish? Why this course? 1) Because it is my absolute favorite opening! 2) I didn’t want to focus on theoretical content but on showing you my soul connected to these positions. That’s my vision in chess, and that’s what I want you to learn from me: my passion for discovering something new, exploring chess, and uncovering treasures in any position. 3) As you probably know, I’m retired from chess competitions and have taken on new roles as a commentator and coach. I’m working with German super-talent Vincent Keymer and have assisted many World Championship finalists. The games and opening analysis I’m presenting here are all mine. It is my work, developed over decades of study with my team, without holding anything back. How to study this course? My main idea is to pass this world-class knowledge on to you, and I want you to learn from this content regardless of your level. I encourage you to watch the videos as many times as necessary to absorb the essence of the positions. I hope my insights are valuable for both the aficionado and the experienced player. Throughout the course, I’ll ask you hundreds of questions about ideas, plans, and maneuvers for both sides in this amazing opening. I’ll challenge you to find the move in the spirit of the position. Feel free to take up the challenge from the very beginning or take it easy, learn at your own pace, and test yourself when you are more familiar with the themes.} *

