1. Z0 {Let me say a few words about 'Cemento.' Those of you following my commentary in recent years are well aware of my 'Cemento spirit.' Still, for those of you who are new to the concept, my recommendation is to get familiar with it as quickly as possible! � In my first ever Chessable course, I tried to focus on providing all my Super Grandmaster Strategy insights into Leko's Ruy Lopez. My intention was to stick with the topic and try to talk as little as possible about 'Cemento' (who knows, maybe in the future we will have a separate 'Cemento project' �). Still, it was impossible to hold Cemento back! I think that it can be extremely useful to master this philosophy in order to better understand the deep concepts and how they connect with each other! For this purpose, and to give you a glimpse of what Cemento is capable of, I decided to select two very special 'Cemento conceptos' from this course: 1) Bc2-b3 Cemento [/variation/38693756] 2) Nd2-b1 Cemento [/variation/38693757] Two completely different styles, but they have one thing in common: the desire to stabilize the situation and gain the benefit no matter how complex it is! 'True Cemento spirit'! Let's have a look at the following positions. I hope that I can infect you with all the positives of the 'Cemento spirit' and that you will be able to use it to your advantage in your games! Enjoy the course!} *

