1. Nb1 $3 {Here, [/variation/38289911/#/1/w] in different Chigorin positions, we see how true art can restrict all of Black´s ideas! Systematically, with each move, we ensure that Black will not get his desired counterplay on the queenside. The stunning positional plan with Re1-e3 allows us to push b2-b4 (the c3-pawn needs to be defended!) to stop Black's strategic plan of getting ...c5-c4, ...Na5-b7-c5 regrouping successfully implemented. We ensure that whenever the black knight moves to b7, we will be able to control it with the timely b4 pawn move! Clearly, Black will try everything in order to succeed in opening up the queenside (trying to get access to the c5-square!) . ) Still, we have one bigger asset in our hands, namely the stunning retreating Nd2-b1 move when White makes sure to 'Cement' the queenside to his advantage! In another example, [/variation/38289909/#/13/w/0.5.0.3] we see how allowing the ...axb4, cxb4 structure on the queenside can also be beneficial for White! First, we keep the a-file closed(!); secondly, we make sure that again, the black knight on b7 is restricted by the b4-pawn; and last but not least, in this case, we get the fantastic opportunity to transfer one of our knights to c3 (via Nf1-g3-e2-c3 or Nf3-d2-b1-c3) with perfect Cemento!} *

