19. Nc3 {Let's test your defensive and calculation skills! Be cold-blooded and precise like an engine! How should Black defend?} Qe8 $1 {Key defensive move!} 20. Qf3 {I stopped here and thought that if Black is ready to play like this, I am up for the challenge! White has beautiful compensation for the exchange. How to defend like an engine here with Black?} h6 $3 {Engines are cold-blooded! It is the only move; otherwise, Black loses.} 21. Bf4 Kg8 22. Re1 Kh7 {There are some spectacular lines here, but Black holds in all of them!} 23. Bxh6 $5 (23. Rxe6 Qd7 24. Bxh6 Rae8 $1 25. Be3 Rxe6 26. Qh3+ Nh5 27. Bxe6 Qd3 28. g4 Bxc3 $1 {Getting access to the ...Qe4+ idea!} 29. gxh5 Qb1+ 30. Kg2 Qe4+ {probably ends with perpetual check.}) 23... Bxh6 24. Rxe6 {What to play now with Black?} Rf8 $3 25. Rxe8 Raxe8 {Suddenly, Black gets serious counterplay!} *

