19... Qc7 {Black is hoping to have time to stabilize with moves like ...a5, ...g6, ...Rbd8, and ...Bb7, and it might not be so easy to break Black's construction. So, White is obviously better, but what could be an effective way to increase the pressure before Black stabilizes?} 20. Nd3 $1 {I love this move so much! In my mind, I keep the memory of this being the decisive move of the game. All the funnier that engines don't even put it into the top 3 category! Engines' chess is something completely different....} ({Clearly I was tempted to play} 20. c5 $5 {immediately, but after} Nxc5 21. Bxc5 dxc5 {White has nice compensation, but there is no need to rush things. The computer highlights that here} 22. g3 $3 {is a very strong move, but this is too sophisticated...}) 20... c5 {This stops our c5 push but has an important flaw.} (20... Ne5 21. c5 $1 Nxd3 22. Rxd3 dxc5 23. Red1 {Total domination on the d-file.}) (20... a5 {Whatever Black was doing, the sleeping beast on b3 would be awakened! We'll see this next.}) 21. Ba4 {Followed by Nd3-f4 and the d5-square is 'eternal'.} *

