20... a5 {Whatever Black was doing, the sleeping beast on b3 would be awakened! How to play?} 21. c5 $1 {Black is just lost.} Bb7 (21... Rbd8 {runs into} 22. Bg5 $1) (21... Nxc5 22. Nxc5 dxc5 23. Bxc5 Bxc5+ 24. Qxc5 Rb5 25. Qd6 {The position is also losing in the endgame.} Qxd6 26. Rxd6 Kf8 27. Red1 {Black is completely paralyzed, and White is in no rush to cash in, can just slowly increase the pressure.}) 22. Bf4 $1 {I sensed that instead of suffering, Shakh is trying to kick out with a quick ...Ba6 idea, and I have prepared a nasty surprise...} Ne5 {This would have prolonged the battle, but the torture would remain.} (22... Ba6 $6 {Shakh fell into my nice little trick (which we'll see next), but we are anyway talking about a horrible position.}) 23. cxd6 Bxd6 24. Nxe5 Bxe5 25. Bxe5 Rxe5 26. f4 {Mobilizing our powerful center.} Re7 27. e5 c5 28. Rd6 {I agree with computer's + 2.30 evaluation.} *

