22... Ba6 $6 {Falling into my nice little trick, but we are anyway talking about a horrible position. How did I win?} 23. cxd6 Bxd6 24. Bxd6 Qxd6 {And here comes my prepared nasty trick.} 25. Ne5 $1 {Great feeling to play a move like this. Now the White rook enters the 7th rank with decisive impact!} Qxe5 26. Rxd7 Red8 27. Red1 {White has total domination. Mamedyarov had had enough of this torture and simply resigned the game. Finishing the tournament with such a stylish strategic win gave me very good emotions, and as an added bonus, it won me the daily Best Game Prize!} *

