18. Qe2 {Black has a stunning sequence to undermine White's center, which made White players switch to a different setup against the Breyer. What is it?} c6 {If Black succeeds in forcing White to release the tension with dxc6, he will achieve everything he dreams about with all his pieces coming to life!} 19. c4 cxd5 20. cxd5 {And now, the critical blow.} Nbxd5 $3 {This is what Spassky had in mind when choosing 16...Nb6 against Judit. What a stunning positional piece sacrifice; this had an earth-shattering impact back in 1993!} 21. exd5 Nxd5 {I was exactly 13 years old when this happened in the legendary Polgar-Spassky Match in Budapest 1993. It is one of those eternal moments!} *

