26... Ba6 {Black's king is in trouble. Here comes an important sub-question: what to do here with White?} 27. Re3 $3 {The rook is joining the battle on the 3rd rank with devastating effect!} (27. Nh4 Kh8 $14) (27. Bxa6 Rxa6 28. Re3 {This is possible as well, but here, Black has better chances of defending. 28.Nh5? Too much talent! In a clearly better position, there's no need for such attitude! 28...gxh5 29.Re3 Nf8 30.Nh4 Ng6 31.Nf5 f6 Black is in time to defend against the mating attack.}) 27... Nf8 28. Nh4 {Simple chess. We are still threatening with either Ngf5 or Nh5 sac...} (28. Nf5 $5 gxf5 29. Nh4 $3 f4 30. Nf5 f6 31. Qxf6 h6 32. Rc3 Bxf1 33. Kxf1 Ra7 34. Rbb3 $3 {This is some insane computer line which is absolutely unnecessary, but I had to show it because it was so beautiful...}) 28... f6 (28... Kh8 29. Ngf5) 29. Nh5 Qf7 30. Nf5 $1 {Lovely position!} gxf5 {Now White can choose between different finishes.} (30... gxh5 31. Nxd6) 31. Rg3+ (31. Nxf6+ Kh8 32. Nxe8 Rxe8 33. Qxd6 {wins as well.}) 31... Kh8 32. Rg7 Qxh5 33. Qxh5 Kxg7 34. Bxa6 {Winning because the bishop is taboo!} *

