27... Qxb8 {Important to think here, as White has a great attacking idea!!} 28. Ng5 $3 {Pretty bombastic! There is even this motif, something that we rarely see. There's no mating threat on h7, but... now, White is threatening to sac the knight with Nh5, and Black is completely helpless. Here we see why it was so important to distract Black's queen from the 7th rank!} (28. Qg5 $5 {Intending Nh5.}) (28. Nh5 $5 gxh5 29. Ng5 $3 {is the same idea. Black could try} h4 {here to stop Rg3.}) 28... cxd5 {A sample line to illustrate White's idea.} 29. Nh5 $1 gxh5 30. Rg3 {There is no escape for Black's king.} h4 {Now, this comes late.} (30... Ng6 31. Qxh7+ {That's why White needed the knight on g5!}) 31. Ne6+ ({And mate!} 31. Nxh7+ {also does the job.}) *

