25... Nf8 {Black is planning to cover the dark squares on the kingside with ...f7-f6. It is always very important to understand what resources our opponent has in mind so that we are getting ready for it both over the board and also psychologically. How to proceed with White?} 26. h4 {A very natural attacking move. I faced some problems here because there were too many other attractive good options as well. But finally, I decided to be practical and play the most systematic way without going for any direct sacrifices.} (26. Re3 $5 {One of the other attractive alternatives. As we know from the other line we looked at, this is a very dangerous idea.}) (26. Nh4 $5 {Also very interesting, but since White can attack without sacrificing anything, there is no need to give Black practical chances! Often, finding only moves to survive is much more preferable for the defending side than to keep defending a simply bad position without perspective.}) (26. Nh2 $2 Bc8 $1 {This is solid for Black.}) 26... cxd5 $6 {In a higher sense, this is already the losing inaccuracy! As we will see later in the game, this trade with ...cxd5, cxd5 will also clearly favor White here as well... But the drawback is kind of still unforeseeable!} (26... Bc8 $1 {was the way to go.} 27. Rxb8 Qxb8 28. h5 Qc7 29. Nd2 $1 {keeping all options open.}) 27. cxd5 Bc8 {Let's try to think about what has changed with the insertion of ...cxd5, cxd5 moves!} 28. Rxb8 $1 {First step. It is always important to force the Black queen to lose time!} Qxb8 29. h5 Qc7 {What now?} 30. Nd2 $3 {Here we see the drawback of the ...cxd5 trade. Suddenly, the c4-square is available for the knight, from which it puts tremendous pressure on the d6-pawn. It is my favorite move in the game. The rest plays like a beautiful melody!} Bd7 {Black's bishop tries to reach the b5-square to control c4, but it is one move too late!} 31. Nc4 $1 Bb5 {Again, a good moment to think! How to proceed?} ({We'll see} 31... f6 {next.}) 32. Nf5 $3 {As usual, when we play a great strategic game, the tactics come to us!} gxf5 33. Nxd6 {Black's position is collapsing!} *

