23... h5 $2 {Now the big question is: is playing Be3xc5 desirable for White or not?} 24. Bxc5 $1 {The answer is absolutely yes! We also know the reasons why because we have a nice light-squared blockade, so we talk about pawn weaknesses instead of potential counterchances!} dxc5 {Honestly, I was spoiled with good options here, but since Black has a clear plan with ...Ne8-d6 I did not hesitate too long on my choice... What where my tempting options?} 25. Qg5 $1 {I instantly fell in love with this move, as it makes it so difficult for Black to achieve his knight maneuver.} (25. Nf1 $5 {If 25. Qg5 did not exist; then clearly, I would have played like this.} Ne8 26. Ne3 Bh6 27. Nf5 {beautiful! Or 26...Nd6 27.Nc4 and we achieve what I have been talking about previously; if we get a blockade on the c4-square, we are happy! In this case, both of Black's bishops are only spectators, not actors!}) *

