25... Rc7 {Setting up a trick... Let's try to understand what Black has in mind and why the e5-pawn isn't just hanging! If we have realized Black's trick, then what is our move?} 26. Nf1 $1 {Exactly, let us just start our strategically winning maneuver!} ({A)} 26. Bc4 {Sets up a fancy idea, but since White is happy there is no need for us to change the character of the battle!} Ne8 27. Qxg6 $5 fxg6 28. d6+ Kf8 29. dxe7+ Kxe7 30. Nh4 Kf6 $1 {and ...Bh6.}) ({B)} 26. Qxe5 $2 Nxd5 $1 {The e5-pawn wasn't hanging!}) 26... Rac8 27. N1d2 {I knew that after natural moves I would be very happy. That is why one always needs to look out for some kamikaze continuation from the opponent...} Ne8 {The normal move.} ({The kamikaze line I wanted to be sure to have under control was} 27... c4 {. What did I calculate here? I'll test you in the next exercise.}) 28. Qxe7 Rxe7 29. Nc4 {I was in time to control everything. Black has many pawn weaknesses, and the black knight was not in time to get to d6...} *

