15... b4 {How did I continue here?} 16. Nf5 $1 {Now Black's position is simply falling apart because he needs to waste one tempo on stopping Nd2-c4! Small but decisive nuance!} Rc8 {Necessary move, but in this case, White gets the extra tempo needed to make maximal use of the f5-knight!} 17. Nf1 {Maybe I could have played better in the next moves, but it was simply impossible to choose from so many great options. Besides, I was surprised myself how big an advantage I got thanks to knowing the 15. a2-a4 finesse.} (17. Nf3 $5 {Somehow exactly this move I had not on my radar!} Re8 18. Bf4 $1) 17... Re8 ({The game went} 17... Nc5 18. N1g3 {For some reason, I did not consider 18.Bf4+- , probably I was too happy...}) 18. Bf4 Bf8 (18... Ne5 19. Nxe7+ Rxe7 20. Ng3 $16 {is strategically huge for White.}) 19. Nxd6 {It is important to calculate this accurately.} Bxd6 20. Bxd6 Bxe4 21. Bxe4 Nxe4 22. Bxb4 $1 {It was quite important to understand from the distance that this works, and basically calculating this line took my attention away from the other alternatives...} *

