33. b4 $1 {Black needs to find a very important idea here. Take your time!} Re6 $1 {Very important move! It destroys White`s hope to jump out thanks to some tactical trick.} (33... f5 $2 {This natural move, with the attitude of let's close the eyes and go, would spoil everything! We'll see how White can punish it.}) (33... Kg7 $5 {is also good with a similar spirit to}) (33... Re6 $1) 34. Re2 {Defending the 2nd rank, but now White's knight is not so effective fighting the black pawns!} Kg7 $5 {Again making one more prophylactic move before starting to push the pawns.} (34... f5 {also possible already.}) 35. Rd1 $5 {Setting up a trick...} Kf6 $1 {The king joins the action!} (35... f5 $2 {fails again, but that's another future question!}) *

