20... Bxe4 {How can White bring extra pieces to the attack?} 21. Rxe4 $1 {The rook is joining the attack on the 4th rank!} Be7 22. Rh4 Nf8 {Only move not to get checkmated, but now White can simply grab the third pawn and get a clear advantage.} 23. dxe5 {Collecting a third pawn.} Qxd1+ 24. Rxd1 N6d7 25. Bxe7 Rxe7 26. Rg4+ {Followed by f4. This is close to winning after both 26...Kh8 27.f4 and 26...Ng6 27.f4 .} *

