19... exd4 {Play the move in the spirit!} 20. e5 $3 {The key move of White's piece sac. Now, modern engines are giving in a fraction of a second all the critical lines for which we had to work like crazy... The concept is obvious: White sacrifices the e-pawn in order to make sure that Black`s b7-bishop stays buried.} (20. cxd4 $2 {is simply met by} dxe4 21. Bxe4 Bxe4 22. Rxe4 Rxe4 {and Black trades the white rook, preventing it from joining the attack.}) 20... Rxe5 21. Rxe5 Nxe5 22. cxd4 {The ideal structure for White in order to get his attack going. This comes with a tempo and, very importantly, the b7-bishop is buried and the c2-bishop is alive.} *

