25... Nxc2 {White has a simple way of getting a winning position. How to play?} 26. Bxf6 {This is technically winning.} ({A more complicated solution is} 26. Nh5 $5 Be7 27. Nxf6+ Kg7 {and next, I challenge you to find White's follow-up.}) 26... Be7 27. Bxe7 Qxe7 28. Rc1 {Simple chess.} Ne1 {The knight is trapped.} (28... Nxd4 29. Qxd5 {with a double attack.}) 29. Qc3 Nxg2 30. Kxg2 $16 {Black's king is vulnerable, the c7-pawn is hanging, the knight is stronger than the bishop.. White has an overwhelming advantage. Often knowing that we have an easy, practical solution helps a lot instead of trying to remember some mysterious winning lines from the computer.} *

