26... Ne4 {Special puzzle, only for those willing to take up the challenge. It might take you days! I couldn't believe my eyes when I saw it - this comes from the engine. If you go straight to read the solution, hold on to your chair first!} 27. Bd2 $3 {Another stunner. The most obvious explanation would be a mouseslip. But no, it's winning! Now the queen can join.} (27. Bh7+ $3 {Spectacular.} Kxh7 28. Qxf7+ {or 27...Kf8 28.Bf4! Qf6 29.Nf5 Some other computer brilliance, but it is still pretty much unclear to a human brain...}) 27... Nxd2 (27... Nc6 28. Qh5 {is winning.}) 28. Qg4+ Kf8 {When we know this is winning, the next move is not hard to find.} 29. Bh7 $1 {The point of White's play.} Ke8 30. Nf5 {And Black has no good defense.} Ne4 31. Nxd6+ Nxd6 {There's no mate, but Black is lost. This can be grasped by humans.} (31... cxd6 32. f3 {I was a bit confused because there is no direct knock-out blow, but simply the position is hopeless for Black.} Nf6 33. Qg5 {controlling the king's escape route.} Kd8 34. Qg7 Nxh7 35. Qxf7 Nc6 36. Qxh7 {is hopeless.}) 32. h4 {Black is paralyzed, so White just wins thanks to the h-pawn!} *

