17. Bd3 {Black has a very powerful sequence here to solve all the opening problems.} bxa4 $3 {This is a stunner because, in 99 out of 100 cases, it would be a big strategic mistake! Again, knowing the details matter!} (17... c6 18. Qc2 Nh5 19. Bf1 {with the typical strategical fight.}) 18. Rxa4 d5 $3 {Now, thanks to a spectacular tactical shot, this Breyer break works to perfection!} 19. dxe5 Nxe4 20. Nxe4 dxe4 21. Bxe4 Bxe4 22. Raxe4 {Looks like Black has miscalculated, but...} Nxe5 $3 {Amazing shot!} 23. Nxe5 (23. Rxe5 Bxe5 24. Qxd8 Raxd8 25. Rxe5 Rxe5 26. Nxe5 Rd1+ 27. Kh2 Rd2 {This double attack is the point.} 28. Ba3 Rxf2 29. Bc5 Rc2 30. Bd4 c5 $1 {breaking the queenside structure was the last important detail with an easy draw in the game [/variation/[ https://www.chessable.com/variation/38709600/#/1/w ]] Vachier Lagrave, M (2734)-Caruana, F (2795) Saint Louis 2023. �}) (23. Qxd8 Nxf3+ 24. gxf3 Rexd8 {gives White nothing.}) 23... Qxd1 24. Rxd1 Rxe5 25. Rxe5 Bxe5 {Thanks to White's vulnerable queenside pawns, it is an easy draw, as happened in the game [/variation/38709601] Firouzja, A (2778)-Le, Q (2728) Miami 2022.�} *

