12... g6 {Black is aiming at the thematic ...Nb8-...Nd7 regroup but, against this move order, White has a powerful idea.} 13. Ba2 $1 {Due to the pressure on the f7-pawn, black is unable to do the Breyer regrouping with ...Nc6-b8-d7! This line is dangerous for Black and worth studying with White. Once we know this is the key vs. 12...g6, the mistake that happened to Firouzja can never happen to us!} Nb8 $2 ({Better is} 13... Bg7 14. b4 {. White also has quiet options like 14.Rb1!? and 14.Qc2!? getting ready to play b2-b4 in the next move. How to punish the Breyer spirit now?}) 14. Ng5 $1 {Officially a novelty, but I guess everybody knows about it by now.} Re7 15. Nxf7 $1 Rxf7 16. Nf3 $1 {There is no good way of stopping Nf3-g5.} Nbd7 17. Ng5 d5 {Black tries to block the Spanish bishop.} 18. exd5 e4 {Trying to keep everything closed.} 19. d6 {Opening up the diagonal for the a2-bishop.} Nd5 20. Nxf7 Kxf7 21. dxc7 Qxc7 22. Rxe4 {This is simply winning for White.} *

