23. cxd5 {No tactics! Black is better. Just try to find moves for him to improve his position.} Rab8 {Black got everything he could only dream about. White is paralyzed, and the space advantage is worth absolutely nothing. All of Black's pieces do a perfect job.} 24. Ba3 {This move highlights how much trouble White is in. White can't do anything but wait till Black keeps on improving his position.} Qd8 $1 {I love moves like this! Black gets perfect harmony.} 25. Qf3 {How to improve Black's position?} h5 $1 {Another typical improving move. Black wants to play ...Bh6 but first makes sure to get the pawn to h5 because, in the long term, Black needs the h-pawn in action!} 26. Raa1 Bh6 {What a picturesque position. Even if I wanted to set up a more ideal position for Black, it would simply be impossible; the last remaining missing move is...} 27. Rab1 Rxb1 28. Rxb1 {Which move creates the perfect harmony in Black's camp?} Kg7 $1 {...this! The perfect harmony. The great thing about strategically overwhelming advantages is that often, with simple good moves, we can suffocate the opponent like a Boa! White is completely helpless...} *

