15. b3 {Now that Magnus stopped the ...Bf8-h6 idea, he is switching back to classical ideas. What are Black's options?} Nxe4 $1 {David apparently got very excited about all these piece sacrifices, which I have told him in our post-mortem.} (15... c6 16. c4 cxd5 17. cxd5 Nexd5 $2 18. exd5 Nxd5 19. Bd2 {or 16...Rc8 17.Ne3 $14 is simply nice for White.}) 16. Bxe4 f5 17. Ng5 (17. Bc2 {was the game continuation.}) 17... fxe4 18. c4 {This is a positional way of handling the situation, and the computer suggests it, but it is humanly not that impressive.} Nf5 19. Nxe4 Qd7 {I understand why Magnus preferred to go for the complications instead because, practically, this position does not look so clear. Black has both ...Nf5-d4 and also ...c7-c6 ideas...Usually, I am a big fan of the e4-square, but here with Black having the pair of bishops, one really has the feeling that this is just unclear.} *

