16... Nd7 $1 {) This is the line Moro has played in the past, hoping for a double-edged play connected with the typical ...f7-f5 break. This is a very complex position, but during my prep, I noticed that thanks to engine precision, White can hope to create problems for Black. How?} 17. a4 $1 (17. Nf1 f5 $1 {Black takes over with this typical strike.} 18. exf5 Nxd5 19. b4 N7b6 20. Be4 Qd7 $15 {was the game [/variation/38709604] Polgar,J-Morozevich Mainz rapid 2008.�}) 17... f5 18. b4 $1 {In fact, this strong move is still a novelty; the idea is to open up the a2-g8 diagonal.} Nf6 19. Bb3 $1 {One of those mysterious engine moves... Well, when we see the move, we can easily make sense of it! Here it is, eyeing the g8-king, and thanks to small tactics, White can keep his vulnerable center together!} Kh8 20. Nh4 {With very sharp play, but I was ready for and very much looking forward to it.} *

