13. Bc2 {How should Black handle this position?} exd4 $1 {This is the justification of 12...Na5, and indeed, it is now getting popular in the 2020s! Back at the beginning of the 2000s, this would have been a real shock... Giving up the center just like this without any real concrete benefit...} (13... c5 $2 {This is just wrong. My opponent treats the position just like after 12.Ba2, but now there are different rules! We'll see this next.}) 14. cxd4 b4 $1 {This is the justification! Suddenly, the knight on a5 is a beautifully placed piece!} 15. e5 {The point is that Black is ready for this.} (15. b3 g6 16. Bb2 Bg7 $13 {is a very interesting position. I believe this whole line will become quite topical as happened now in the game [/variation/38709610] Zilka-Vitiugov, 2023. �}) 15... dxe5 $1 16. dxe5 Nd7 $132 {The position is out of control! Black gets the nice c5-square for his knight.} *

