13... c5 $2 {Black's move is just wrong. My opponent treats the position just like after 12.Ba2, but now there are different rules! What's White's best reaction?} 14. d5 $1 {Whenever the bishop is on b7 in these types of positions, this is the first move we should look at!} c4 15. b4 $1 {I was very happy about this opportunity, blowing the queenside open and changing the character of the position.} (15. Nf1 Nd7 {gives Black what he wants with eternal counterplay due to the b3-square!} 16. Be3 Qc7 {and ...Nc5 is coming.}) 15... cxb3 16. Nxb3 {During the game, I had no idea how good my position was; I was just trying to play in the right spirit.} Nxb3 (16... Nc4 {White has a strong reply here. We'll see it in another exercise.}) 17. Bxb3 Nd7 (17... Qc7 {We'll see this in another exercise.}) 18. c4 $1 {Everything goes according to the plans...} *

