23. Bb5 {This looked so good for White during the game that we both completely missed the ideas that super-engines are showing now. Any good ideas for Black?} Qc7 $3 {The move we both missed during the game! Suddenly, there is no good way to protect the e4-pawn, and a special move per move battle starts (engines territory!).} 24. Nd2 {During the game I was sure that this should be better for White, but now versus engines I can't prove anything...} Bc8 (24... Ba6 25. Bc6 Bb7 26. Rxb4 Bxc6 27. Bxc5 $1 dxc5 28. Rxb8 Rxb8 29. dxc6 $14 {The knight is better than the bishop and White has the important d5-square.}) (24... Ra2 $5 25. Re2 Ba6 $1 26. Rxb4 Qa5 $1 27. Bxc5 dxc5 28. Rb1 Bxb5 29. cxb5 Rxb5 30. Rc1 Qa4 $1 {is a very computerish solution because if White stabilizes here, he will get a big advantage, but comp move per move holds it...} 31. Qxa4 Rxa4 32. Nc4 Rbb4 33. Rec2 {is almost over, but in the analysis, we are dealing with an engine!} g6 $1 {provokes the d5-d6 move.} 34. d6 f6 $1 {and by miracle Black holds this!}) 25. Qc2 Ra3 $132 {And the engine sees no way to claim an advantage! Again, the b4-pawn is safe.} *

