23... c3 $2 {It takes only one inaccuracy, and White again gets the upper hand! How did Moro exploit Shakh's mistake?} 24. Re3 $3 {Brilliant! Moro spots his chance instantly! This is a multi-purpose move targeting the c3-pawn and setting up the powerful Nd4-f5 sacrifice!} Nb6 $6 {As often, mistakes come in bunches...} (24... Ne5 25. Nd4 Nfd7 26. Rb3 {would win the c3-pawn.}) 25. Nd4 $1 Nfd7 26. Ngf5 $1 {This might have been even stronger than Moro's choice.} (26. Ndf5 $1 {This is a typical piece sacrifice in many of the Classical Spanish positions when White is active, and Black´s pieces are far away from the kingside. Shakhriyar eventually bailed out into a terrible position, but didn't get mated.}) 26... Be5 27. Bxe5 Nxe5 28. Qc1 $5 {Not the only good move, but a nice one!} Kh8 29. Rg3 {With a terrible attack.} *

