16... Bf6 {Now, the big question: how to proceed with White? Grischuk shows an impressive concept!} 17. Ng3 $1 {I give the exclamation mark because of the deep concept that Grischuk had in mind by playing this knight move right away! The first reaction could easily be like, why do we force or provoke ...g6, which seems to be very useful for Black? The next question is: why do we want our knight on g3?} g6 18. Rb1 $1 {Here it comes!} c5 19. d5 {The Benoni structure.} Nc4 20. Nh2 $1 {I believe Sasha was very well prepared and knew exactly what and why he was doing it! White's idea is to keep Black's pieces hanging in the air for one move! Black has to show his cards: will it be ...Bg7 or ...Nde5? Not an easy choice.} (20. b3 $5 {According to my analysis from 2016, this move order is also possible, but I appreciate Grischuk's spirit of keeping things as simple as possible!}) *

