26... Nf8 {Black protects the f7-pawn according to the plans, but White is all set. How to play?} 27. e5 $1 {Now finally, when everything was ready, Grischuk goes for the break!} dxe5 28. f5 $1 {I know it is typical, but aesthetically it is always extremely beautiful!} Bg7 {Finally, Black gives in to trade the dark-squared bishops. That shows the seriousness of the situation...} 29. Bxg7 Kxg7 {Obviously, White has many strong continuations. The choice Grischuk made signals me that he had already foreseen the beautiful mating net he went for.} 30. f6+ Kh8 31. Rbd1 $1 {Including the last piece into the game!} *

