31... Rd7 {Let's try to think and understand which spectacular idea Grischuk had in mind.} 32. Qe3 $1 {The move is easy, but actually it requires extreme precision!} Nxd5 33. Rxd5 $1 {Only thanks to this sacrifice does White achieve his aim!} Rxd5 34. Qh6 Ne6 {Did Sasha miss something? Black only needs ...Rg8 and ...Qf8, and the queen will be kicked out of h6! Is White really able to set up a killing threat in just two moves?} 35. Ne4 $1 Rg8 {But now what? ...Qf8 is coming...} (35... Rd4 36. Ng5 $1 {wins on the spot.}) 36. Nf3 $3 Qf8 37. Nfg5 $3 {What a fantastic finish! I am such a big fan when, with a good opening understanding, one builds up the pressure step by step and delivers such a masterpiece!} Nxg5 (37... Qxh6 38. Nxf7#) 38. Nxg5 Rg7 {The only move, but it equals resignation.} (38... Qxh6 39. Nxf7#) 39. fxg7+ Qxg7 40. Nxf7+ {And Black resigned!} *

