16... c5 {This runs into tactical problems! How to punish Black now?} 17. e5 $1 {This is the problem.} dxe5 (17... Be7 $2 18. exd6 Bxd6 19. a3 Nc6 20. dxc5 Bxc5 21. Qc2 {and the double threat is decisive.}) 18. dxc5 $1 Na4 19. a3 $1 Nc6 {And here comes the power of the knight on e3... What is the key move for White?} 20. Nd5 $3 {Simple and effective! Suddenly, everything makes perfect sense!} Nxc5 (20... Be6 21. Nxf6+ gxf6 22. Qc2 {hitting h7 and threatening to trap the knight with b2-b3 or 21...Qxf6 22.Bg5+- and the queen is trapped.}) 21. Nxf6+ gxf6 22. Nh4 Z0 ({With very strong initiative.} 22... e4 23. Qh5 Re5 24. Qh6 {Black has too many problems! Instead, 22.Qc2 e4! is not so clear.}) *

