14... g6 $2 {I consider this natural move already as the losing mistake! How should White proceed?} 15. d5 $1 {It is time to close the center, thus making the f6-bishop dead! Also Black has no good square for his knights, plus there is one more factor...} (15. Ng4 {would destroy all the spirit I had been playing for!} Bxg4 $1 16. hxg4 exd4 $1 17. cxd4 Nb4 18. Bb1 c5 $132 {Now Black is ready for counterplay.}) 15... Na5 {How to continue?} 16. Ng4 $1 {Yes, after ...g7-g6 has been played, we can go after Black´s king!} Bxg4 ({I already had something very special in mind against} 16... Bg7 {We'll see it next.}) 17. hxg4 {With ...g6 played and the center closed, g4-g5 is a strong possibility, while Black has no counterplay.} *

