15... Ba6 {) It is very important to be familiar with the ideas. White has a very thematic knight maneuver worth knowing.} 16. Nh2 $5 ({It is common knowledge that this is the key move in this line. However, when checking with new super engines, things are again different from how we thought about them earlier.} 16. Nc2 {is not the right way.} Nc5 17. Nb4 Nxb3 18. Qxb3 Bc8 {intending ...Bd7 and ...Qb7, or 18...Bb7 preparing ...c6. There is also another interesting option with 16.Be3!? Nc5 17.Bc2 and b4.}) 16... Ng6 17. Ng4 {Hitting the bishop gives us a big tempo; at least, that was the deep knowledge we had!} ({Actually, now the engine suggests another way with} 17. Ba2 $5 {This is one of those super-clever prophylactic moves that only computers can think of... Now} Rb8 $6 18. Nc2 $1 {is strong, and 17...Qd8 is met by some very deep play by engines... 18.Nf3! The idea is obvious: Black was threatening to trade the dark-squared bishops with ...Bf6-g5. Suddenly, the engine claims that White has everything under control and should be happy.}) 17... Be7 18. Ne3 $3 {Amazing. The knight journey continues!} Rb8 (18... Bg5 $1 {The engine plays spoiler and claims it is not so bad! Here is a logical, high-quality model line.} 19. Qg4 Qd8 20. Bc2 Bf4 $1 {and it is not so simple, as ...Nf6 is coming.} 21. g3 Nf6 22. Qf3 Bxe3 23. Bxe3 Qc8 24. h4 h5 25. Bb1 Ng4 26. Nc2 Qa8 27. Nb4 Bc8 28. Bd2 f5 29. exf5 Ne7 $132 {.}) 19. Nec2 $3 {I find this knight route so incredibly beautiful.} Nc5 20. Nb4 Bc8 (20... Nxb3 21. Qxb3 {with pressure on the queenside thanks to Nc6 ideas.}) 21. Nc6 {Honestly, I remember that we discussed this incredible knight maneuver with Zoltan Almasi already back in the 96-97 period!} (21. Nc6 Rb6 22. Bc2 Bd7 23. b4 Nb7 24. Be3 Rxc6 25. dxc6 Bxc6 26. Bc1 {is the legendary Dominguez-Svidler game [/variation/38709621] from 2015. �}) *

