19... Bxd5 {How should White continue targeting Black's poor structure?} 20. Nf3 $1 {My concept! It is always extremely pleasing to make moves like Nf3-d2 and, in the next move, to return with Nd2-f3 after we have achieved what we wanted!} (20. Ne4 $5 {is the modern engines' choice... More about this in the annotated game.}) 20... Be6 {Here, I was planning to continue in style.} (20... Bxf3 {This is capitulation, but Black´s position was falling apart, and obviously, the Nd2-f3-d2-f3 maneuver had its psychological effect!}) ({After} 20... Bc6 {White can play both} 21. Qe2 {or 21.Bf5!? and Black can't keep his weaknesses together.}) 21. Be4 $1 (21. Nxe5 Nxe5 22. Qxd8 Raxd8 23. Rxe5 Bf6 24. Re3 $16 {The black rook has no entry points .}) 21... Rb8 {The engine's solution is another shock...} (21... Rc8 22. Bb7) 22. Bc6 $5 (22. Bd5 {This was my original plan, and is also winning.} Bxd5 23. Qxd5 Qc7 24. Nxe5 Nxe5 25. Bf4 $1 {was what I intended.} Rbd8 26. Bxe5 Rxd5 27. Bxc7 Bf6 28. Re3 {and White should win this easily.}) 22... Qc7 23. Bxd7 $1 {It is never easy to give up our soul for a pawn, but it is not only about the pawn...} Bxd7 24. Nxe5 {White gets very quickly Bf4 and Qf3 with devastating developments.} *

