31... gxf6 {White has all the fun here. When there's more than one winning way, look for something really beautiful!} 32. Bg5 $1 {The fun continues!} Re6 (32... Rxa1 33. Bxf6+ Kg8 34. Bxd8 {and White wins.}) 33. Re1 $1 {These are all the reasons why I decided on 28. Rxe5 earlier.} Rdd6 34. Rxe6 Rxe6 35. Bf4 Nd7 {Now, White is winning in many ways, but is there something really beautiful?} (35... Re8 36. b5 axb5 37. Bxb8 Rxb8 38. a6) 36. Bd5 $1 Re2 {Here comes more beauty!} 37. Bxc4 $1 {I could not resist!} (37. Be3 Ne5 38. b5 axb5 39. a6 {and this passed pawn is again winning.}) 37... Re4 38. Bd3 $1 Rxf4 39. Kg3 $1 {I just loved that I could win the game with such a quiet little king move, which traps Black`s rook in the center!} *

