12... exd4 {Morozevich's try. White should just play normally instead of trying to be extra smart! How would you continue?} 13. Nxd4 Re8 14. Nc3 $1 {Kamsky was well prepared against Moro's dubious line.} (14. Bg5 h6 15. Bh4 Nd5 $132 {I run into this in my game [/variation/38718700] Leko-Morozevich, Wijk 2002. �}) 14... Bb7 15. Nf5 $1 {Immediately going after Black's throat!} Bf8 (15... Rc8 $2 16. Bg5 $1 {and now} b4 {is best, as it is only bad but not losing... The natural 16...Nc4? , the idea of Black's play, is already losing! 16...h6? 17.Bxf6! is a huge problem 17...Bxf6 18.Nxd6+-}) 16. Qf3 $1 (16. Bg5 h6 $1 17. Bh4 Rc8 18. Qd4 Re6 {protecting f6 is actually pretty ok for Black.}) 16... h6 (16... Rc8 $2 17. Bg5 $1 {is winning now with the Nh6 threat.}) 17. Rd1 $1 {With nice advantage, but it is still a game.} *

