18... Nh5 {Black wants to create counterplay with ...f7-f5, but it is too slow! Why?} 19. a4 $1 f5 ({In the game, Black tried to hang on to the b5-pawn with} 19... Qe8 {but when White is given free hand in such cases, the question is only when does Black's position collapse...}) 20. axb5 axb5 (20... f4 21. Ba7 {Famous! Ever since the legendary Karpov game we know that we have this square in the Spanish Chigorin...}) 21. Bh6 {Anticipating ...f4. Next, White can capture the b5-pawn.} Z0 (21... Rf7 22. Bxb5 {and the b7-knight is too sad.}) *

