19... Qe8 {Black tries to hang on to the b5-pawn, but when White is given a free hand in such cases the question is only when does Black's position collapse... How to play?} 20. axb5 axb5 21. Ra7 Rb8 22. Bh6 Ng7 23. Qe2 {Total domination.} Nd8 {The reason why people often do not mind having the terrible knight on b7 in the Chigorin is that they hope to transfer it to f7 via ...Nb7-d8-f7 after ...f7-f6. However, this plan can only work with a closed queenside; if White already has a target, it will never be satisfactory!} 24. Rc1 $1 {I still remember how happy I was about this move!} (24. Nxb5 {was winning a pawn already, but I felt that this pawn was not running away...}) *

