1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O Be7 6. Re1 b5 7. Bb3 O-O 8. c3 d6 $6 {Losing the psychological battle. Mickey should have stuck to his beloved Marshall! I have noticed that whenever Black over the board decides to deviate from his main weapon, the Marshall, out of fear that the opponent might have prepared something special, it almost always ends badly! After all, there is a real reason why Marshall players prefer to play the Marshall...} 9. h3 Na5 {I think I can speak in everyone's name that compared to a Marshall, the Spanish Chigorin is a very welcome gift to all of us!} 10. Bc2 c5 11. d4 Qc7 {Keeping the tension is considered the most reliable line for Black.} 12. Nbd2 {The move that I have been using all my life.} cxd4 13. cxd4 Nc6 {By now, I believe that this is Black's most reliable line in the Chigorin. Luckily, before this game, I was still very optimistic about White's chances here. Sometimes, being an optimist is so much better than being objective...Black immediately puts the pressure on the d4-pawn.} 14. Nb3 {The absolute main line.} (14. d5 $2 {would be premature. My first question for you will be... why?}) *

