19... Bd8 {A thematic idea in this line, but in this position White has a good way of countering it. How to play?} 20. Qe2 h6 21. dxe5 $1 {Well-timed trade!} dxe5 22. Bd3 $1 {Targeting the b5-pawn and inviting Black to lose his coordination. In general, White´s idea in this line is to combine pressure against the weak b5 & e5-pawns. Somewhere, White is also dreaming to use the Rc1-c5 idea!} Nb4 23. Bb1 Bb6 (23... Nc6 24. Red1 $14) 24. Red1 Bxe3 25. Qxe3 {This is promising for White. The e5-pawn is vulnerable.} *

