25. Nxb5 {Does Black have a good move here?} Nc4 $1 {This is not so simple.} 26. Nc7 (26. Nxc4 Qxb5 27. exd5 Nxd5 {is good for Black thanks to the queenside pawn structure and the pressure on the e-file and the a6-f1 diagonal.}) 26... Qxc7 27. exd5 Nxd5 28. Rxc4 Qd7 $1 29. Qd3 Rad8 {White is better, but this is less convincing.} *

