24. Bg5 {A challenging test for your calculation skills! What does the engine have in mind here?} Nxe4 $3 {Incredible, but engines almost always find some special way to deal with every position.} 25. Bxe4 f5 26. Bd3 e4 27. Be2 Nxd5 ({The point. Black's position is falling apart after} 27... exf3 28. Bxf3 {with ideas like Nd4 for White, and the vulnerable e7-square.}) 28. Nfd4 f4 $1 {And, due to many dynamic factors, the position is completely out of control.} 29. Z0 (29. Bg4 h6 30. Bh4 {and Black has many possibilities to continue with 0.00s.} Nc3 31. Qd2 Bxg4 32. hxg4 Qd5 33. Ra6 Na4 $1 {protecting the b6-bishop is a stylish engine line. Not very instructive, but sensational!}) *

