32... Ra8 $1 {Black's only practical chance! How should White proceed here?} 33. Bxg7+ $3 (33. Rf1 $2 {Terrible choice (the move itself is not bad), especially because at the beginning, I had some 30 minutes left and calculated for 20 minutes all the fantastic lines after the sacrifice with 33. Bxg7. All my calculations turned out to be perfectly correct, but since I knew that I was simply winning here, finally, I did not dare to trust my calculation; luckily, I won the game; otherwise, it would be really difficult to forgive myself for not trusting myself!} Nce8 $1 {Now Black is in time to defend the kingside. Of course, the position is terrible; White is a pawn up after all, but now the time trouble is coming, and psychologically, I was pretty down that my dream of delivering checkmate did not materialize...}) (33. Rxa8+ Qxa8 34. Be3 Bxe3 35. Qxe3 {should be winning.}) 33... Kxg7 {Here, it was very difficult to decide which knight should give a check on f5, as both look good, but both moves give extra options for Black.} 34. Nhf5+ (34. Nef5+ Kf8 {is tricky, but I'll leave it for you to solve in the next exercise.}) 34... Kh7 (34... Kf8 {White wins with almost the same idea as after 34.Nef5+ Kf8 .}) 35. Rxa8 Qxa8 36. Qg3 Bxf5 37. Qh4+ $1 {This wins on the spot.} *

