39. g4 $5 {Black had a golden opportunity to defend the position with a totally counterintuitive move. How could Black have held here?} Bxe3 $3 {Giving up the dark-squared bishop like this is something that does not cross our minds, especially not in extremely heavy time trouble! But here it has a very concrete idea...} ({Gata played} 39... Nh7 $2 40. Kg2 {My time trouble has finished! But not his, and his 40th move was very unlucky, as we'll see.}) (39... Kf8 40. Nxg6+ $1 fxg6 41. g5 $16) 40. Qxe3 (40. Bxe3 Qc3 $1 {The other concrete idea.} 41. Kg2 Qxb4 42. Nc6 Qa4 {looks beautiful for White, but in fact, there is no clear way to crack Black's position; the computer even goes as far as to claim the 'famous 0.00s'. 41.Qe2! Qxb4 42.Qc2! is the computer precision still asking tough questions!}) 40... Kf8 $1 {Now this is possible.} 41. Nc6 Bxc6 42. dxc6 Qxc6 {Rock solid. Despite White having the two bishops, Black is probably holding this without much trouble.} *

