40... Qb7 $2 {The famous move 40, played with few seconds on the clock! Black wants to play ...Bb6-d8 and feels secure enough on the kingside but runs into a very unpleasant surprise! Why was this such an unlucky move? Take your time to calculate! We're in move 41�} 41. Nc4 $3 {It took me exactly 32 minutes to come up with this stunning shocker! This is one of the main reasons why I have always been and am a huge fan of classical time control. Dealing with all the emotions after the time-trouble, getting enough time after move 40 is essential! Once I managed to calm down and stopped blaming myself for all the missing winning options, suddenly it hit me that there was a golden opportunity to make up for all the previous pain!} bxc4 ({A)} 41... g5 {This is equal to capitulation, but Gata did not want to give me the chance to deliver my beautiful mating idea. It is a pity... You can see the rest of the game next.}) ({B)} 41... Bxg4 42. Bh6+ $1 {is the same:} Kxh6 43. Qxf7 Bxh3+ 44. Kg3) ({C)} 41... Bd8 42. Na5 $1 Qa6 43. Nec6 {and if 43...Bxa5 again 43.Bh6+! Kxh6 44.Qxf7 with the same problems...}) 42. Bh6+ $3 {The key idea of the whole sacrifice!} Kxh6 43. Qxf7 {And there is no defense against mate with Qxg6.} *

