13. g4 $2 {) One of those rare strategic mistakes from the legendary Bobby Fischer! This is when you are still a bit young, at the same time, already very strong and a tiny bit too ambitious! In general, the idea is impressive; White stops ...f7-f5 and is planning Nbd2-f1-g3 with great prospects. What's the problem?} h5 $1 {The only problem is that on the opposite side sits another legend Paul Keres... and he punishes it immediately!} 14. Nh2 hxg4 15. hxg4 Bg5 {Forcing the trade of dark-squared bishops. Suddenly, White's position is in strategic ruins!} 16. Z0 (16. Nd2 g6 {A small improving move.} 17. Ndf3 Bxc1 18. Qxc1 Kg7 {Obviously, Black is going to attack White on the kingside! White's idea has heavily backfired.} 19. Qg5 {Damage control, but the endgame is also bad...} Nb7 20. Qxd8 Rxd8 21. a4 bxa4 22. Bxa4 Nxa4 23. Rxa4 Bd7 24. Ra2 c4 $1 25. Nd2 Bb5 {happened in the game [/variation/38709634] Fischer-Keres Curacao Candidates 1962. � 19...Qxg5! was even stronger: 20.Nxg5 Nac4 hitting b2, and White has problems after 21.b3?! Na3! 22.Bd3? c4-+ due to the fork on c2, or 21.Rab1 Bd7 $17 where g4 and b2 are weak and Black has a clear plan on the queenside.}) *

