16... Qd7 {The d5-pawn is the soul of the position. If someone is not familiar with the line, then please take time to understand what White's beautiful idea could be!} 17. b3 $3 {This is the lovely little tactic that made me instantly fall in love with the system! Those days, it was not like we opened engines and immediately got the right answer... These little b3-pushes, restricting the black knights, are already familiar, right?} Qb7 {What's White's point?} (17... Raf8 {was how Kramnik played against me in a blindfold. Here, I let a golden opportunity slip. Next, I'll challenge you to improve on my play.}) 18. c4 $1 {Yes, thanks to this trick we can defend our only weakness!} bxc4 $2 {This is not possible.} 19. Bd2 {Suddenly trapping the knight!} *

