17... Raf8 {Even today, I feel quite angry that I let this golden opportunity slip against Kramnik. Looking back, I was very angry at myself for relaxing too much instead of looking for ways to make the most of my chance! How should White play?} 18. Nfg5 $5 {Already during the game, my intuition tempted me for this move, but I tried to control myself and decided to play more routinely... Why is it such a difficult choice? Well, because, in general, I do not fancy the idea of changing my 'good' knight for the 'so-called' bad bishop, but one should also be more alert. After all, only one knight can lend on e4 while the 'bad' bishop is actually doing a good job protecting the weak d6-pawn and, as we will see in the game, it has even a potential route to be activated...} ({Instead, I played} 18. Nh2 Qd8 19. Nf1 $1 {Clever regrouping!} Qa8 20. Ne3 Rf4 21. f3 {I was enjoying myself, as we will see little more than I should have...}) 18... Bxg5 19. Bxg5 {Black's position is so much more vulnerable without the e7-bishop!} Nb7 20. Rc1 $16 ({This was my old move, and I think it is good enough; no need for the unhuman, mysterious} 20. Bc1 {, which is now the top choice of the engines (no comment)}) 20... c4 21. Be3 $1 {Keeping Black under check with his knight!} *

