21... Rf8 {I missed a great chance in a blitz game against Mamedyarov. How should White treat this position?} 22. c4 $3 {It could have been a perfect game.} (22. Bc1 Nxd5 23. Qg3 Nf6 24. Nxd6 Nxd6 25. Rxd6 Nh5 26. Qg4 Rxf2 27. Be3 Rxa2 28. Rd7 {Now Black is ok, but we had very little time, and things escalated...} Qg6 29. Bxc5 Re8 30. Rxe5 {Boom!} Rxg2+ $2 {Hallucination under tension. I had been in Shakhriyar's shoes, now I was the lucky one...} 31. Kxg2 Qc6+ 32. Red5 {and Black resigned.}) 22... bxc4 23. bxc4 Nxc4 {Here comes the stunner!} 24. Nf6+ $3 gxf6 25. Bc1+ Qg6 26. Qxc4 {This is completely winning according to engines because the rook on f5 is kinda trapped and the queenside is falling apart. Also, White even has Rd3-g3 ideas as well.} *

