18... Qf7 {White has a very powerful continuation. Be open-minded!} 19. g4 $5 {It's not easy to play these moves over the board. Instead, I played} (19. b4 $5 {I would hate to give up the c4-square just like this, but I was tempted by seeing a force variation.} cxb4 20. cxb4 Nd8 21. Be3 Nc4 22. Nc7 {This is what I spotted when opting for 19.b4.}) 19... Qg6 {Don't stop here. What's White's follow-up?} 20. Ng3 {Exactly! The rook has to retreat.} Rf7 21. f4 {Opening up the center while the black knights are sadly sitting on the queenside! All this is an interesting computer suggestion.} *

