13... g6 $5 {Black's principal possibility, preparing ...f7-f5. What's White's correct reaction?} 14. Nf1 $1 {The computer likes this!} (14. b4 Nb7 $1 {This has been an important improvement and had been holding on nicely for Black over a decade already. For example:} 15. Nf1 f5 {with total chaos in the game [/variation/38709637] Leko (2699)-Tari (2597) Italian League 2017. � I would like to ask for forgiveness for playing so badly, but at 9 AM, my head is simply not working...}) 14... f5 15. Bh6 Rf7 16. exf5 {This is similar to a King's Indian, but not exactly.} gxf5 17. Ng3 $1 {I have known this for over a decade, but during the 9 AM game, I just realized that I could hardly even know my name... From the stress of needing to wake up so early, I was basically unable to sleep the whole night. That is the real problem... White has a very good position. We won't go into depth here; this is for you to study.} (17. Ng3 $1 Kh8 $5 {I encourage everyone to check these lines carefully because the position is very sharp!} 18. a4 $1 {Opening up a new front should guarantee White the upper hand in this wild position. 17...e4 18.Bxe4!! is still a novelty! 18...fxe4 19.Rxe4 $16 The lines continue, but it is very promising for White. The black king is exposed.}) *

