15... Nb7 {The reason why Black does not mind it is that he counts on an ...a6-a5 break. White seems to be just a tempo short to achieve the desired stability... Take your time to find White's correct reaction.} 16. Nf1 $1 {Very important strategical idea!} (16. a3 a5 17. Rb1 {trying to hold on to the structure does not work.} axb4 18. axb4 Na4 {with concrete problems. 18...Ra2 is also annoying.}) 16... a5 {The reality is that there is no need to look for stability!} 17. a3 axb4 18. cxb4 {In fact, the spoiled structure with cxb4 is very good for White! The most important thing is that there is no counterplay on the queenside; the passed c-pawn goes nowhere, but White's kingside attack will slowly build up. White also has another idea, namely the positional plan of transferring one of the knights to c3! A very important strategic idea to know!} Na4 19. Ng3 {The typical idea of regrouping the horrible b7-knight to f7 is probably the only way to play with Black.} (19. Ng3 Qe8 20. Be3 f6 {and last question in the Classical Spanish for you...}) *

