20... f6 {A lovely thematic exercise to finish the course. Play in the spirit! How to arrange the white pieces?} 21. Nd2 $1 {The knight was doing nothing on f3.} Nd8 22. Nb1 $3 {Again, this amazing move! One should remember this idea because the c3-square in such structures is a key square for White´s knight. Please remember my comment [/variation/38040050/#/16/b/0.3] from the Leko-Hansen game!} Nf7 23. Bxa4 $1 {Giving up the light-squared bishop is never easy, but here we know why!} Rxa4 24. Nc3 {Exactly!} Ra8 25. Qb1 $16 {Very nice move! Keeps an eye on f5, prepares the a3-a4 break, and, just in case, even keeps the 2nd rank open for the rook if needed (Re2-a2 shift).} *

